blog.name: sylispokeworldheadcanons
blog.title: But what if we all did live in a Pokemon world
blog.description: Hi I'm Syli and I think about Pokemon too much. Headcanons about how the Pokemon world might work. May not be 100% canon compatible. I also lift elements from different continuities/adaptations based on what I like. Asks and so forth are welcome, but I might be slow about answering. If you need anything tagged just let me know.

summary:
Ambipom have become the Pokémon of choice for
carrying and operating cameras for filming shots from trees while moving....
body:
Ambipom have become the Pokémon of choice for carrying and operating cameras for filming shots from trees while moving. They’re strong and dexterous enough to handle the camera and keep it steady, and usually more mature than Aipom. That being said, they still can get distracted, and one movie recently had an issue with the camera Ambipom starting a fight with the Passimian in the cast.

Another Pokémon used for getting footage form trees is Ariados. They spin web slings to hold the cameras. One Ariados became well-known in the film industry for webbing the camera to his chest and lowering himself out of trees or from lamp posts to get perfect, eerie shots for horror movies.

Egg Group: Water 2 Ability:...
caption:
Remake of the Castide line. What else is there to say besides it’s a fish!

Type: Water

Egg Group: Water 2

Ability: Marvel Scale, Torrent

Hidden Ability: Water Veil

Castide (Coast Pokemon) are popular Pokemon to keep as pets considering their cute demeanor, sociable nature, and colorful pattern

Ability: Marvel Scale, Torrent

Hidden Ability: Water Veil

Miragill (Cascade Pokemon) swim through the coral reefs showing off the color pallets of their vivid fins. But when they aren’t comparing who’s fin colors are more saturated, they are fighting tooth and nail- sometimes to the death.
